Firstly, you need to create a route in your `routes/api.php` file:

```php
Route::post('password/email', 'PasswordResetController@sendEmail');
Route::post('password/reset', 'PasswordResetController@reset');
```

Then, you need to create a `PasswordResetController`. You can use Laravel's built-in password reset functionality, which is part of the `Auth` package. Here's a basic example:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Password;

class PasswordResetController extends Controller
{
    public function sendEmail(Request $request)
    {
        $request->validate(['email' => 'required|email']);

        $status = Password::sendResetLink(
            $request->only('email')
        );

        return $status === Password::RESET_LINK_SENT
                    ? response()->json(['status' => __($status)], 200)
                    : response()->json(['email' => __($status)], 400);
    }

    public function reset(Request $request)
    {
        $request->validate([
            'token' => 'required',
            'email' => 'required|email',
            'password' => 'required|min:8|confirmed',
        ]);

        $status = Password::reset(
            $request->only('email', 'password', 'password_confirmation', 'token'),
            function ($user, $password) {
                $user->forceFill([
                    'password' => bcrypt($password)
                ])->setRememberToken(Str::random(60));

                $user->save();
            }
        );

        return $status == Password::PASSWORD_RESET
                    ? response()->json(['status' => __($status)], 200)
                    : response()->json(['email' => __($status)], 400);
    }
}
```

This is a basic example and might need to be adjusted to fit your specific needs. Also, remember to import necessary classes at the top of your controller file.

Please note that this code assumes you have set up the necessary email configurations to send the password reset link. If you haven't, you'll need to do that as well.

